Syria says it is ready for the voluntary return of refugees and calls for help to rebuild the country, devastated by a war of more than seven years.
Before the United Nations General Assembly, Foreign Minister Walid al-Moualem said conditions in the country are improving.
Today, the situation on the street is more stable and secure, thanks to the progress that has been made in the fight against terrorism," he said.
The government continues to rehabilitate the areas that terrorists destroyed to restore normality.
All conditions for the voluntary return of refugees to the country that had to be abandoned due to terrorism and the unilateral economic measures that affected their daily lives and their maintenance are met.
The EU estimates that more than 5.5 million Syrians have fled the country since the beginning of the war in 2011.
There are also six million people living in the country and in need of humanitarian aid.
Al-Moualem said that the Syrian regime is grateful for any help to rebuild the devastated country.
But he stressed that he would not accept conditional aid or help from the countries that financed the insurgency.
